==Abstract==

This IIP describes output script descriptors, a language for describing collections of output scripts. It adapts BIP 380 for INTcoin's ML-DSA-87 keys.

==Motivation==

Descriptors provide:
* Unambiguous description of wallet outputs
* Import/export of watch-only wallets
* Derivation of addresses from extended keys
* Multisig wallet coordination

==Specification==

===Basic Syntax===

<pre>
DESCRIPTOR = SCRIPT_EXPR [ "#" CHECKSUM ]
SCRIPT_EXPR = "pk(" KEY ")" | "pkh(" KEY ")" | "wpkh(" KEY ")" |
              "multi(" THRESH "," KEY {"," KEY}* ")" |
              "sortedmulti(" THRESH "," KEY {"," KEY}* ")" |
              "wsh(" SCRIPT_EXPR ")" |
              "addr(" ADDRESS ")" | "raw(" HEX ")"
KEY = HEX_PUBKEY | WIF | XPUB | XPRV
</pre>

===Key Expressions===

'''Hex public key''':
<pre>
pk(0a1b2c3d...)  // 2592 bytes = 5184 hex chars
</pre>

'''Extended public key''':
<pre>
wpkh(ixpub1...)           // All addresses
wpkh(ixpub1.../0/*)       // External chain
wpkh(ixpub1.../1/*)       // Internal chain
wpkh(ixpub1.../0/*')      // Hardened derivation
</pre>

'''With origin''':
<pre>
wpkh([73c5da0a/44'/2210'/0']ixpub1.../0/*)
</pre>

===Script Types===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Descriptor !! Script Type
|-
| pk(KEY) || P2PK (bare pubkey)
|-
| pkh(KEY) || P2PKH (pubkey hash)
|-
| wpkh(KEY) || P2WPKH (witness pubkey hash)
|-
| wsh(SCRIPT) || P2WSH (witness script hash)
|-
| multi(k,KEY,...) || k-of-n multisig
|-
| sortedmulti(k,KEY,...) || k-of-n with sorted keys
|}

===Checksum===

8-character checksum using BCH code:
<pre>
wpkh(ixpub1...)#abc12345
</pre>

===INTcoin Adaptations===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Component !! BIP 380 !! IIP-35
|-
| Extended key prefix || xpub/xprv || ixpub/ixprv
|-
| Public key size || 33 bytes || 2592 bytes
|-
| Signature opcode || OP_CHECKSIG || OP_CHECKSIG_DILITHIUM
|}

===Examples===

Single key:
<pre>
wpkh([73c5da0a/44'/2210'/0'/0/0]ixpub1...)#checksum
</pre>

2-of-3 multisig:
<pre>
wsh(sortedmulti(2,[fp1/48'/2210'/0'/2']ixpub1.../0/*,[fp2/...]ixpub2.../0/*,[fp3/...]ixpub3.../0/*))
</pre>

